&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CROYDON HEALTH SERVICES NHS TRUST&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;CROYDON UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Trust Registrar in Gastroenterology&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Gastroenterology Registrar to work in Croydon University Hospital. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;GMC registration and MBBS &amp; MRCP are essential. Candidates should have some experience in Gastroenterology and a keen interest in supporting service developments. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There is ample opportunity to attend outpatient clinics. Whilst on-call the postholder would be on-call for Acute Medicine. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be required to participate in a General Medical Registrar on call rota as well as undertake ward based duties in renal care and for renal referrals, supervising a team of Foundation Year and Core Medicine trainees. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Within this role you can look forward to a professional structure where we have excellent links with the local GPs and Primary Care Networks, as well as the opportunity to work in a large and developing department with enthusiastic colleagues. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Croydon University Hospital is a busy District General Hospital, serving the population of Croydon. Most Medical and Surgical specialties are represented. There are strong links with local teaching centres and there are many training grade rotations in place. The Trust also has an active postgraduate medical centre and well-stocked library. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition, our Trust is in an excellent location, close to Central London and well situated in the South East. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further information or for an informal chat about the post, please contact Sabrina Easy via switchboard on 020 8401 3000 ext4825&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sabrina Easy - sabrinaeasy@nhs.net/&lt;span&gt;020 8401 3000 ext4825&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
